result.notes: This data shows the number of staff employed at different grades in the Home Office, our agencies and executive non-departmental public bodies, broken down by headcount and number of posts (full-time equivalents). It includes the number of 'non-payroll staff', and the paybill costs relating to staff, broken down into component parts (for example, salaries, allowances, and employer's pensions contributions).

organization.description:
The Home Office leads on immigration and passports, drugs policy, crime policy and counter-terrorism and works to ensure visible, responsive and accountable policing in the UK.

Home Office is a ministerial department, supported by 26 agencies and public bodies.
